---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" description="Bao CLI documentation - Generate CLI applications from TOML">
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <div class="mb-8 md:mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-arcade text-white mb-4">
      INTRODUCTION
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Define your CLI in TOML. Bao generates type-safe code in Rust or TypeScript.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- What is Bao? -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-arcade text-xl text-arcade-cyan mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-arcade-cyan/30">
      // WHAT IS BAO?
    </h2>

    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
      Bao is a CLI generator. You describe your CLI structure in a TOML file, and Bao generates
      all the boilerplate code for argument parsing, help text, and command routing.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
      You write the command logic. Bao handles everything else.
    </p>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border-2 border-arcade-yellow/50 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-black px-4 py-2 border-b border-arcade-yellow/30 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-pink"></div>
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-yellow"></div>
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-lime"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="font-arcade text-[10px] text-arcade-yellow">bao.toml</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm overflow-x-auto bg-arcade-dark"><code class="text-gray-300"><span class="text-arcade-yellow">[cli]</span>
name = <span class="text-arcade-lime">"greet"</span>
language = <span class="text-arcade-lime">"rust"</span>

<span class="text-arcade-yellow">[commands.hello]</span>
description = <span class="text-arcade-lime">"Say hello"</span>

<span class="text-arcade-yellow">[[commands.hello.args]]</span>
name = <span class="text-arcade-lime">"name"</span>
type = <span class="text-arcade-lime">"string"</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="border-2 border-arcade-lime/50 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-black px-4 py-2 border-b border-arcade-lime/30 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-pink"></div>
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-yellow"></div>
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-arcade-lime"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="font-arcade text-[10px] text-arcade-lime">terminal</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm overflow-x-auto bg-arcade-dark"><code><span class="text-arcade-cyan">$</span> <span class="text-arcade-lime">bao bake && bao run -- hello World</span>
<span class="text-gray-400">Hello, World!</span>

<span class="text-arcade-cyan">$</span> <span class="text-arcade-lime">bao run -- --help</span>
<span class="text-gray-400">Usage: greet &lt;COMMAND&gt;

Commands:
  hello  Say hello
  help   Print help</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Bao? -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-arcade text-xl text-arcade-pink mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-arcade-pink/30">
      // WHY BAO?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 border-l-2 border-arcade-lime/50 bg-black/30">
        <span class="text-arcade-lime font-arcade shrink-0">+</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Single Source of Truth</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Define your CLI once. Generate for Rust or TypeScript.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 border-l-2 border-arcade-cyan/50 bg-black/30">
        <span class="text-arcade-cyan font-arcade shrink-0">+</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Handler Preservation</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Regenerate anytime. Your command implementations are never overwritten.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 border-l-2 border-arcade-yellow/50 bg-black/30">
        <span class="text-arcade-yellow font-arcade shrink-0">+</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Type Safety</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Generated code uses clap (Rust) or boune (TypeScript) with full type inference.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 border-l-2 border-arcade-pink/50 bg-black/30">
        <span class="text-arcade-pink font-arcade shrink-0">+</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Nested Subcommands</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Build complex CLIs like <code class="text-arcade-yellow">myapp db migrate --dry-run</code></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Supported Languages -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-arcade text-xl text-arcade-yellow mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-arcade-yellow/30">
      // SUPPORTED LANGUAGES
    </h2>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-arcade-pink/50 bg-black/30 p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
          <span class="font-arcade text-arcade-pink text-lg">RUST</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-xs">+ clap</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Derive-based clap with async support via tokio.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-arcade-cyan/50 bg-black/30 p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
          <span class="font-arcade text-arcade-cyan text-lg">TYPESCRIPT</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-xs">+ boune</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Type-safe TypeScript with the boune CLI framework.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Next -->
  <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-800 flex justify-end">
    <a href="/docs/installation" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-arcade-lime hover:underline font-arcade text-sm">
      Installation <span>&rarr;</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
